`also` is not a keyword, it&#39;s just a function. It can be preferred to `apply` when e.g.:

1. You want to use the current `this` instead of `apply`&#39;s receiver parameter:

        val list = mutableListOf&lt;MyClass&gt;().also { 
            add(this) // won&#39;t work with apply
        }

2. You want to give a name to the parameter:

        mutableListOf&lt;MyClass&gt;().also { list -&gt; ... }

